    <div class="bit-60"> 
     <a id="invest"></a>
     <h2>Invest in an affordable<br> Westmont education</h2> 
     <p>Westmont awarded more than $21 million in financial assistance this year, making our high-quality education accessible to students and families from a wide range of economic backgrounds. In fall 2013, students with demonstrated need received an average award of $28,681.</p> 
    </div> 
    <div class="bit-5"> 
     <!-- This is an empty div --> 
    </div> 
   </div> 
   <div class="frame home-section-one-1"> 
    <div class="bit-5"> 
     <!-- This is an empty div --> 
    </div> 
    <div class="bit-60"> 
     <a href="financial-aid.html"><img src="images/95financialaid.png" alt="financial aid" width="100%"></a> 
    </div> 
    <div class="bit-5"> 
     <!-- This is an empty div --> 
    </div> 
   </div> 
   <div class="frame home-section-one-2"> 
    <div class="bit-60"> 
     <h3>Westmont Consistently Ranks in the Top 100 Liberal Arts Colleges </h3> 
     <p>For the fifth straight year, <strong>U.S. News &amp; World Report</strong> ranked Westmont among the 100 best liberal arts colleges in the nation and the top 10 in California.</p> 
     <p><strong>Kiplinger’s Personal Finance</strong> lists Westmont as No. 83 in 2014 and features colleges that provide high-quality academics at a reasonable cost. Westmont scored well in several attributes that parents and students seek: small class sizes, a good freshman-retention rate and a high four-year graduation rate. </p> 
     <p>Westmont ranks among the best colleges in the west in <strong>Princeton Review’s</strong> 2014 report, which includes 124 colleges in 15 western states (41 in California). Nationwide, Princeton Review ranked only 643 institutions—25 percent of U.S. four-year colleges—in four regions. Princeton noted Westmont’s excellent academic programs and positive reports by students about their campus experiences.</p> 
     <p><strong>Forbes Magazine</strong> ranked Westmont No. 74 among colleges and universities in its survey, Grateful Grads: Top Return-on-Investment. Westmont is one of three Christian colleges nationally and nine schools in California in the top 100. The ranking measures the amount of private gifts given to four-year colleges divided by the number of full-time students.</p> 
    </div> 
    <div class="bit-40"> 
     <img src="images/top100years.png" alt="top 100 seals" width="100%"> 
    </div> 
   </div> 
   <div class="frame home-section-two"> 
