    <div class="bit-60 the-place"> 
     <a id="santa-barbara"></a>
     <h2>This is our place</h2> 
     <p>Perched gracefully between the Pacific Coast beach and the Santa Ynez Mountains, Westmont’s campus offers a great environment for your studies as well as the sun and surf you’ll need for study breaks.</p> 
     <div class="home-button-sb">
      <a href="santa-barbara.html"><img src="images/visit-us.png" alt="visit santa barbara button" width="250"></a>
     </div> 
    </div> 
    <div class="bit-5"> 
     <!-- This is an empty div --> 
    </div> 
   </div> 
   <div class="frame home-section-seven-1"> 
    <div class="bit-60"> 
     <h2>Discover the Difference Between International Education and Global Learning</h2> 
     <p>We’ve developed a unique cycle of global learning for our own programs to help you make the most of your cross-cultural experiences. You’ll spend a semester studying the region before you leave. While you’re there, Westmont professors will guide your learning. When you return, a re-entry seminar will help you embrace, apply and share your insights.</p> 
     <p>Westmont prepares you to be a global citizen equipped to make an impact in the world. About <strong>70 percent</strong> of our students spend a semester off campus or overseas, choosing from <strong>more than 65 programs</strong>.</p> 
     <p><strong><a href="global.html" class="white">Learn more &gt;&gt;</a></strong></p> 
    </div> 
    <div class="bit-40"> 
     <img src="images/cycle-of-global-learning.png" alt="global learning cycle" width="100%" class="global-graphic"> 
    </div> 
